The paper deals with the problem of autonomous driving in a crowded environment, which is a core problem in robotics. The proposed approach involves integrating online POMDP planning and deep learning, which are key areas in robotics and artificial intelligence. The paper also mentions the use of computer vision techniques to handle noisy sensors. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.RO (Robotics), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves learning from data, which suggests the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as likely possibilities.
